column3: Happy 71st birthday to my best friend ❤️ I miss you so fucking much almost nothing else matters. There’s not a single day that goes by that i don’t think about you. I pray to you before every show, and i hope you get to look down and see some of them. All of this is for you. Making you proud is my single most important achievement in life, making you laugh. It’s hard to enjoy anything without sharing it with you. But i refuse to believe I’ll never see your scruffy face or hear your voice ever again. I miss you so much man, i wish you’d come back. Losing you is the most pain i imagine a person can feel, but it’s made me not afraid of death. If the worst thing that can happen to me is be reunited with you, thank God. But… I’ve got a lot more memories to make before then and i can’t wait to tell you all about them someday. I love you Papaw ❤️

column3: COLUMBUS, OH❤️ Long grateful post: The first comedy show i ever saw was @danecook at @nationwidearena when i was 14. That show made want to be a standup comedian, and i started the next year at the local comedy club. I wrote an email to Dane’s public fan email address the following year. Not truly believing he’d even read it…he not only responding with a budding thank you and well wishes…he saved the letter…and we read it on stage together this past Saturday, for the first time in 14 years. On top of an incredible full circle moment, I also broke the record for most tickets ever sold at one show by any performer ever at the same Arena 15 years later😮‍💨 Over 19,000 people. What a beautiful Homecoming 🙏🏼🥹 I LOVE Y’ALL O-H… #comedy #standup #mattrife #columbus #ohio

column3: This is what comedy’s about- light and laughter no matter what. Bianca’s gratitude at the end melted my heart. ❤️ Before you get offended for somebody else, maybe get to know them and see how they actually feel. I met this lovely young lady at my San Diego show and she was the epitome of why we do comedy- to make people feel seen, or understood, and most importantly laugh to lighten the weight of what life throws at us.🫶🏻 You can be offended all you want, but in comedy, i don’t know that there’s anything more offensive than treating someone as if they’re not good enough to be included. And if humor isn’t for you, cool… keep it pushing. Don’t deprive others of their happiness. #comedy #standup #standupcomedy #funny #mattrife #crowdwork #sandiego #handicap

column3: Happy 71st birthday to my best friend ❤️ I miss you so fucking much almost nothing else matters. There’s not a single day that goes by that i don’t think about you. I pray to you before every show, and i hope you get to look down and see some of them. All of this is for you. Making you proud is my single most important achievement in life, making you laugh. It’s hard to enjoy anything without sharing it with you. But i refuse to believe I’ll never see your scruffy face or hear your voice ever again. I miss you so much man, i wish you’d come back. Losing you is the most pain i imagine a person can feel, but it’s made me not afraid of death. If the worst thing that can happen to me is be reunited with you, thank God. But… I’ve got a lot more memories to make before then and i can’t wait to tell you all about them someday. I love you Papaw ❤️

column3: COLUMBUS, OH❤️ Long grateful post: The first comedy show i ever saw was @danecook at @nationwidearena when i was 14. That show made want to be a standup comedian, and i started the next year at the local comedy club. I wrote an email to Dane’s public fan email address the following year. Not truly believing he’d even read it…he not only responding with a budding thank you and well wishes…he saved the letter…and we read it on stage together this past Saturday, for the first time in 14 years. On top of an incredible full circle moment, I also broke the record for most tickets ever sold at one show by any performer ever at the same Arena 15 years later😮‍💨 Over 19,000 people. What a beautiful Homecoming 🙏🏼🥹 I LOVE Y’ALL O-H… #comedy #standup #mattrife #columbus #ohio

column3: This is what comedy’s about- light and laughter no matter what. Bianca’s gratitude at the end melted my heart. ❤️ Before you get offended for somebody else, maybe get to know them and see how they actually feel. I met this lovely young lady at my San Diego show and she was the epitome of why we do comedy- to make people feel seen, or understood, and most importantly laugh to lighten the weight of what life throws at us.🫶🏻 You can be offended all you want, but in comedy, i don’t know that there’s anything more offensive than treating someone as if they’re not good enough to be included. And if humor isn’t for you, cool… keep it pushing. Don’t deprive others of their happiness. #comedy #standup #standupcomedy #funny #mattrife #crowdwork #sandiego #handicap
